<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
popularly known as Pitu, Bristled River Shrimp and Buchura River Prawn, is a freshwater shrimp species widespread along the eastern coasts of the Americas. The species can be found from the southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[296,446,820,843]" name="United States of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">United States</collectingCountry>
, where the prawns were introduced (
<bibRefCitation author="Holthuis" box="[868,1208,820,843]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Holthuis, L. B. &amp; Provenzano, A. J. (1970) New distribution records for species of Macrobrachium with notes on the distribution of the genus in Florida (Decapoda, Palaemonidae). Crustaceana, 19 (2), 211 - 213. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854070 X 00545" type="journal article" year="1970">
Holthuis &amp; Provenzano, 
<number box="[1151,1208,820,843]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), southwards to Rio Grande do Sul (
<collectingCountry box="[323,393,855,878]" name="Brazil" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), including numerous records in 
<collectingCountry box="[749,833,855,878]" name="Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[845,957,855,878]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[969,1088,855,878]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1101,1188,855,878]" name="Panama" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1200,1308,855,878]" name="Colombia" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1319,1431,855,878]" name="Venezuela" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,234,889,912]" name="Guyana" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Guyana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[285,387,889,912]" name="Suriname" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">Suriname</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Holthuis" box="[402,564,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1952) A general revision of the Palaemonidae (Crustacea, Decapoda, Natantia) of the Americas II. The subfamilies Palaemonidae. Occasional Paper, Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, 12, 1 - 396." type="journal article" year="1952">
Holthuis, 
<number box="[508,564,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1952.0">1952</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[575,743,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Williams, A. B. (1984) Shrimps, Lobsters, and Crabs of the Atlantic Coast of the Eastern United States, Maine to Florida. Smithsonian Institution Press. 550 pp." type="book" year="1984">
Williams, 
<number box="[686,743,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Melo" box="[753,879,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Melo, G. A. S. (2003) Familias Atyidae, Palaemonidae e Sergestidae. In: Melo, G. A. S. (Ed.), Manual de identificacao dos Crustacea Decapoda de agua doce do Brasil. Editora Loyola, pp. 289 - 415." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Melo, 
<number box="[822,879,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Valencia" box="[890,1174,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Valencia, D. &amp; Campos, M. R. (2007) Freshwater prawns of the genus Macrobrachium Bate, 1868 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Palaemonidae) of Colombia. Zootaxa, 1456, 1 - 44." type="journal article" year="2007">
Valencia &amp; Campos, 
<number box="[1116,1174,889,912]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
This species was described about two hundred years ago by Arend Friedrich August 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiegmann" box="[1114,1310,924,947]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Wiegmann, A. F. (1836) Beschreibung einiger neuen Crustaceen des Berliner Museums aus Mexico und Brasilien. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 2, 145 - 151." type="journal article" year="1836">
Wiegmann, (
<number box="[1252,1310,924,947]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1836.0">1836</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1321,1364,924,947]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="150.0">150</number>
), from specimens collected on the “Brazilian coast”, with no further location details. Its taxonomic history is complex with a long list of rearrangements and synonymies (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Holthuis" box="[715,883,993,1016]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1952) A general revision of the Palaemonidae (Crustacea, Decapoda, Natantia) of the Americas II. The subfamilies Palaemonidae. Occasional Paper, Allan Hancock Foundation Publications, 12, 1 - 396." type="journal article" year="1952">
Holthuis, 
<number box="[826,883,993,1016]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1952.0">1952</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[899,964,993,1016]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="96.0" valueMax="97.0" valueMin="95.0">95-97</number>
; references above). Due to a great many morphological variations, misidentifications and uncertainties that were detected around the relationship and the evolution of this species, members of this group are categorized as the 
<taxonomicName box="[921,1032,1062,1086]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersii">
<emphasis box="[921,1032,1062,1086]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">M. olfersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (
<bibRefCitation author="Rossi" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Rossi, N. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2013) Molecular analysis of the freshwater prawn Macrobrachium olfersii (Decapoda, Palaemonidae) supports the existence of a single species throughout its distribution. PLoS ONE, 8 (1), e 54698. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0054698" type="journal article" year="2013">
Rossi &amp; Mantelatto, 
<number box="[1375,1432,1063,1086]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2013.0">2013</number>
; Rossi &amp; Mantelatto, in prep.
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
Although many of the numerous taxonomic controversies have been corrected in recent years by a combination of different analyses, the nomenclature of this species still appears troubled. In recent systematic literature treating the species, two spelling variants exist: with two “i” (
<taxonomicName box="[684,759,1200,1224]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersii">
<emphasis box="[684,759,1200,1224]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">olfersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="De" box="[819,1111,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="De Grave, S. &amp; Fransen, C. H. J. M. (2011) Carideorum catalogus: the recent species of the dendrobranchiate, stenopodidean, procaridean and caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda). Zoologische Mededelingen, 89 (5), 195 - 589. Avaliable from: http: // www. zoologischemededelingen. nl / 85 / nr 02 / a 01 (Accessed 23 May 2016)" type="journal article" year="2011">
<collectingCountry box="[819,850,1201,1224]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">De</collectingCountry>
Grave &amp; Fransen, 
<number box="[1055,1111,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rossi" box="[1121,1399,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Rossi, N. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2013) Molecular analysis of the freshwater prawn Macrobrachium olfersii (Decapoda, Palaemonidae) supports the existence of a single species throughout its distribution. PLoS ONE, 8 (1), e 54698. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0054698" type="journal article" year="2013">
Rossi &amp; Mantelatto, 
<number box="[1344,1399,1201,1224]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) as an ending or only one (
<taxonomicName box="[399,467,1235,1259]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersi">
<emphasis box="[399,467,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">olfersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pileggi" box="[525,821,1236,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Pileggi, L. G. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2010) Molecular phylogeny of the freshwater prawn genus Macrobrachium (Decapoda, Palaemonidae), with emphasis on the relationships among selected American species. Invertebrate Systematics, 24 (1), 194 - 208. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 09043" type="journal article" year="2010">
Pileggi &amp; Mantelatto, 
<number box="[764,821,1236,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pileggi" box="[831,1038,1235,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Pileggi, L. G. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2012) Taxonomic revision of doubtful Brazilian freshwater shrimp species of genus Macrobrachium (Decapoda, Palaemonidae). Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 102 (4), 426 - 437. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0073 - 47212012005000012" type="journal article" year="2012">
Pileggi 
<emphasis box="[913,960,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[980,1038,1236,1259]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,750,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">
This nomenclatorial confusion is obviously not of recent making, as numerous examples exist throughout the literature of either spelling variant, but clearly not linked to any biological discipline. We noted that the two distinct names can be found throughout different research studies with no consistent usage within the same discipline. Here we list some examples which adopted 
<taxonomicName box="[523,626,1374,1398]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersi">
<emphasis box="[523,626,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">M. olfersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(- 
<emphasis box="[650,657,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">i</emphasis>
) or 
<taxonomicName box="[702,812,1374,1398]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Macrobrachium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olfersii">
<emphasis box="[702,812,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">M. olfersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(- 
<emphasis box="[837,852,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">ii</emphasis>
). Studies involving physiology used - 
<emphasis box="[1256,1263,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">i</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Augusto" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Augusto, A., Greene, L. J., Laure, H. J. &amp; McNamara, J. C. (2007) The ontogeny of isosmotic intracellular regulation in the diadromous freshwater palaemonid shrimps, Macrobrachium amazonicum and M. olfersi (Decapoda). Journal of Crustacean Biology, 27 (4), 626 - 634. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1651 / S- 2796.1" type="journal article" year="2007">
Augusto 
<emphasis box="[1376,1422,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[151,206,1409,1432]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) but also - 
<emphasis box="[326,341,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">ii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lima" box="[357,551,1408,1432]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Lima, A. G., McNamara, J. C. &amp; Terra, W. R. (1997) Regulation of hemolymph osmolytes and gill Na + / K + - ATPase activities during acclimation to saline media in freshwater shrimp Macrobrachium olfersii (Wiegmann, 1836) (Decapoda, Palaemonidae). Journal of Experimental Marine Biology and Ecology, 215 (1), 81 - 91. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0022 - 0981 (97) 00016 - 6" type="journal article" year="1997">
Lima 
<emphasis box="[424,473,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[495,551,1409,1432]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="McNamara" box="[565,864,1409,1432]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="McNamara, J. C. &amp; Torres, A. H. (1999) Ultracytochemical location of Na + / K + - ATPase activity and effect of high salinity acclimation in gill and renal epithelia of the freshwater shrimp Macrobrachium olfersii (Crustacea, Decapoda). Journal of Experimental Zoology, 284, 617 - 628. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1002 / (SICI) 1097 - 010 X (19991101) 284: 6 &lt;617 :: AID-JEZ 3&gt; 3.0. CO; 2 - V" type="journal article" year="1999">
McNamara &amp; Torres, 
<number box="[807,864,1409,1432]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In reproduction aspects- 
<emphasis box="[1147,1154,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">i</emphasis>
was used by Mossolin &amp; Bueno (
<number box="[234,290,1444,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2002.0">2002</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation box="[349,600,1443,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Magalhaes, T., Mossolin, E. C. &amp; Mantelatto, F. L. (2012) Gonadosomatic and hepatosomatic indexes of the freshwater shrimp Macrobrachium olfersii (Decapoda, Palaemonidae) from Sao Sebastiao Island, Southeastern Brazil. Pan-American Journal of Aquatic Sciences, 7 (1), 1 - 9." type="journal article">
Magalhães 
<emphasis box="[470,517,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[537,593,1444,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
but - 
<emphasis box="[656,671,1444,1467]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">ii</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[710,932,1443,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Ammar, D., Muller, Y. M. R. &amp; Nazari, E. M. (2001) Biologia reprodutiva de Macrobrachium olfersii (Wiegmann) (Crustacea: Decapoda: Palaemonidae) coletados na ilha de Santa Catarina, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Biologia, 18 (2), 529 - 537. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81752001000200024" type="journal article">
Ammar 
<emphasis box="[798,845,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[865,923,1444,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Morphological and development larval studies used either - 
<emphasis box="[289,296,1479,1502]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">i</emphasis>
(e.g. Nazari 
<emphasis box="[444,494,1478,1502]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[517,574,1479,1502]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2003.0">2003</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Simoes-Costa" box="[588,874,1478,1502]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Simoes-Costa, M. S., Pacheco, C., Nazari, E. M., Muller, Y. M. R. &amp; Ammar, D. (2005) Estagiamento de embrioes de Macrobrachium olfersi (Wiegmann) (Crustacea, Palaemonidae) atraves de criterios morfologicos nos dias embrionarios. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 22 (2), 501 - 508. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81752005000200029." type="journal article" year="2005">
Simões-Costa 
<emphasis box="[746,803,1478,1502]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[819,874,1479,1502]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) or - 
<emphasis box="[932,947,1479,1502]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">ii</emphasis>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dugger" box="[1014,1287,1479,1502]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Dugger, D. M. &amp; Dobkin, S. (1975) A contribution to knowledge of the larval development of Macrobrachium olfersii (Wiegmann, 1836) (Decapoda: Palaemonidae). Crustaceana, 29 (1), 1 - 30. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854075 X 00018" type="journal article" year="1975">
Dugger &amp; Dobkin, 
<number box="[1231,1287,1479,1502]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" refString="Anderson, G. &amp; Filingame, J. A. (1980) The occurrence of Macrobrachium olfersii (Wiegmann, 1836) and Macrobrachium carcinus (Linnaeus, 1758) in Southern Mississipi, U. S. A. (Decapoda, Palaemonidae). Crustaceana, 39 (1), 90 - 94. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854080 X 00319" type="journal article" year="1980">
Anderson &amp; Filingame, 
<number box="[274,331,1513,1536]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Müller 
<emphasis box="[423,472,1512,1536]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[493,551,1513,1536]" pageId="0" pageNumber="587" value="2003.0">2003</number>
). In ecology and general biology, - 
<emphasis box="[929,936,1513,1536]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="587">i</emphasis>
